Every year, around 240 million 9-1-1 calls are answered by emergency dispatchers in the United States. On National 9-1-1 Telecommunicators Day, the contributions of these dedicated men and women are honored. This year is the 50th anniversary of the first 9-1-1 call, which was made on February 16, 1968 in Haleyville, Alabama. Since then, emergency communication services have improved and expanded to better respond to various situations. Today, 9-1-1 services are available to about 97 percent of the United States. Technological advancements have made the system more widespread and efficient, allowing dispatchers to provide rapid response and timely assistance. National 9-1-1 Telecommunicators Day serves as a reminder to thank and recognize these emergency dispatchers for their invaluable service in protecting lives and property.